# Rasm Dependencies

## C# central package management

- Versions live in `Directory.Packages.props` only — `.csproj` declares usage, never versions
- Check truth: `rg -n "<PackageId>" Directory.Packages.props Directory.Build.props **/*.csproj`
- Add `PackageVersion` only when a concrete consumer exists — no future-intent entries
- Validate: `dotnet restore Workspace.slnx --locked-mode` (removals) or normal restore (graph changes)
- RhinoWIP host assemblies via `Directory.Build.props` app-bundle refs — not universal NuGet

## TypeScript catalog

1. `rg -n "dep" pnpm-workspace.yaml` (catalog)
2. Add exact version to catalog if missing
3. Reference as `"catalog:"` in package.json
4. `pnpm install` → `pnpm exec nx run-many -t typecheck`

## External-lib-first

- Approved manifest deps are first-class — integrate native APIs end-to-end
- Check `docs/system-api-map` before `System.*` additions
- Check `docs/external-libs` before LanguageExt/Thinktecture/MathNet usage
- Never hand-roll what approved libraries already own; never thin-wrap external APIs

## Key pinned packages (see Directory.Packages.props for truth)

- LanguageExt.Core 5.0.0-beta-77, Thinktecture.Runtime.Extensions 10.2.0
- MathNet.Numerics/Symbolics 6.0.0-beta2, CSparse 4.3.0 (Rasm only)
- xUnit v3, CsCheck, coverlet, Verify, ArchUnitNET, BenchmarkDotNet, SharpFuzz
